messages.content: Tell me a fun fact about Octopuses.

A fun fact about octopuses is that they have three hearts! Two of the hearts pump blood to the gills, where the blood is oxygenated, and the third heart pumps the oxygen-rich blood to the rest of the body. This unique system helps them thrive in their underwater environment. Additionally, their blood is blue because it contains hemocyanin, which is more efficient than hemoglobin in cold, low-oxygen waters.
